A man was shot to death in the Bronx following a dispute, police said. Police responding to the call found the victim, 28, outside a public housing project at 1465 Washington Avenue at 10:43 a.m. Saturday. He was shot in the chest and pronounced dead after being taken to St. Barnabas Hospital. His last known address was in Harlem. Police are searching for a man wearing a white shirt and a woman in burgundy pants who fled the scene.